{
  "texts": [
    "Human agency cannot be forcefully modified in this way.",
    "A teenager's parents cannot take away the teenager's capacity to engage in social interactions.",
    "At best, they can take away the teenager's typical means to do that (e.g., by grounding them or seizing their mobile).",
    "But since this leaves the teenager's relevant capabilities unchanged, the teenager can still exercise those capabilities when the circumstances allow for it.",
    "Replika's ability, in contrast, has been lost once and for all-unless future updates reintroduce it, of course."
  ]
}